4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH AND CELEBRATING THE LIFE OF ILA
5 FRANCES KIMBRELL CORNELIUS.
6
7 WHEREAS, the death of Mrs. Ila Frances Kimbrell
8 Cornelius of Thomasville, Alabama, on February 21, 2026, is
9 noted with sadness, and her 84 years of life are commended
10 and celebrated with thanksgiving; and
11 WHEREAS, Mrs. Cornelius was born on August 2, 1941,
12 in Columbus, Mississippi, to Basil Manning and Maureen
13 Funderburk, and was raised in a manner that reflected the
14 values she later demonstrated in her life and work; and
15 WHEREAS, she devoted a portion of her life to the
16 field of education, serving as an educator and positively
17 influencing the youth through her dedication, guidance, and
18 commitment to learning; and
19 WHEREAS, Mrs. Cornelius was a member of Thomasville
20 United Methodist Church, where her faith was an important
21 part of her life; and
22 WHEREAS, left to cherish her memory are her husband,
23 Theodore Reid Cornelius; sons, Pat Cornelius and Reid
24 Cornelius; daughter, Amy Cornelius Carlisle; grandchildren,
25 Abby Cornelius Boothe, Ethan Cornelius, Sam Cornelius, Bryce
26 Carlisle, Darby Cornelius, and Brock Cornelius; and
27 WHEREAS, Mrs. Cornelius was a valuable member of the
28 community who loved her home and her family and who formed
Page 1

community who loved her home and her family and who formed
HR296 INTRODUCED
29 many special friendships through the years; she will be
30 sorrowfully missed, but the memory of her good deeds remains
31 and she will be forever treasured in the hearts of those
32 whose lives she shared; now therefore,
33 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
34 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That while mourning the death of
35 Mrs. Ila Frances Kimbrell Cornelius, it is comforting to
36 remember her long and abundant life, and this resolution is
37 offered to her grieving family with heartfelt sympathy.
